jdrew.oo.util
Class RuleML88Parser

java.lang.Object
  jdrew.oo.util.RuleML88Parser
class RuleML88Parser
extends java.lang.Object

This class implements the back-end parser for the RuleML 0.88 (+ rests) format. Currently this is the only version of RuleML that is supported in OO jDREW; Back-end parsers for other version may be added in the future.

Title: OO jDREW

Description: Reasoning Engine for the Semantic Web - Supporting OO RuleML 0.88

Copyright: Copyright (c) 2005

parseFact

private DefiniteClause parseFact(Element atom,
                                 boolean newVarnames)
                          throws ParseException
This method is used to parse a fact element, creating a new variable name list if indicated. Typically a new variable list is wanted; but in certain cases (such as parsing an inner clause in an assert) the same variable list must be used.

Parameters:
atom - Element The XOM Element objec that represents the fact to be parsed.
newVarnames - boolean If true a new variable names list is created and used; otherwise the current variable name list is used.
Returns:
DefiniteClause A DefiniteClause data structure that represents the fact in a way that can be used by the reasoning engine.
Throws:
ParseException - Thrown if there is a serious error parsing the fact.
